04574nam a22006375i 9780823295623DE-B159720230103011142.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230103t20212000nyu    fo  d z      eng d  a97808232956237 a10.1515/97808232956232doi  a(DE-B1597)575309  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anyucUS-NY 7aBIO0180002bisacsh1 aAnderson, George M., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aWith Christ in Prison :bFrom St. Ignatius to the Present /cGeorge M. Anderson. 1aNew York, NY : bFordham University Press, c[2021] 4c©2000  a1 online resource (248 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tCHART OF IMPRISONED JESUITS BY COUNTRY OF INCARCERATION -- tPREFACE -- tINTRODUCTION -- tONE Voluntary Incarceration -- tTWO Ignatius's Own Experience and Ecclesiastical Prisons -- tTHREE Arrest and Trial -- tFOUR Spectators -- tFIVE Joyful Acceptance of Incarceration for Christ's Sake -- tSIX Physical Suffering and Torture -- tSEVEN Jesuit Brothers -- tEIGHT Prayer in Prison -- tNINE Mass -- tTEN Daily Order -- tELEVEN Work -- tTWELVE Ministry -- tTHIRTEEN Guards -- tFOURTEEN Becoming a Jesuit in Prison -- tFIFTEEN Community in Prison -- tSIXTEEN Conclusion -- tGLOSSARY -- tBIBLIOGRAPHY -- tINDEX0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe book provides an account of many Jesuits, from the time of St. Ignatius to the 1990’s, who have been incarcerated around the world for their faith. It is divided into chapters that deal with specific themes related to their imprisonment. The principal themes are: prayer as a key element in survival, arrest and trial procedures, the experience of suffering, Mass, the daily order of prison life, forced labor, ministry to other prisoners, guards, prisoners who became Jesuits while imprisoned, community in prison, and voluntary incarceration.This is the first book to examine the experience of incarcerated Jesuits around the world and down through the centuries from the standpoint of these various themes. Much of the material is by the Jesuits themselves, in letters, autobiographical fragments and other sources—including obscure publications long out of print. The result is a gathering together of these pieces and fragments into a coordinated whole, with commentary on their significance in the context of the political and cultural situations of their time—situations that were generally the immediate cause of the Jesuits imprisonment, whether in Elizabethan England or in Communist China and Russia. A chart of imprisoned Jesuits by country of incarceration at the beginning, and a glossary of names at the back (as well as an index), will help the reader to keep track of the names of the many Jesuits who figure in the book.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Religious.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311118960408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831107072980 cprintz978082322065640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082329562340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823295623423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823295623/original  a978-3-11-070729-8  Fordham University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-118960-4  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK